markdown_instructions.U3L24 Chatbot Conditionals 3_markdown_in:
## Chained Conditionals

Now we have a bot that responds to anything and has a special response to the color blue. How can we add a special response for more colors? By using an `if`/`else if`/`else` statement (read "if" ... "else if" ... "else"). By adding an `else if` statement, we create a chained conditional. 

<details>
<summary>**Example**</summary>
<pre>`	if (yourResponse == myResponse) {
    	setText("text_area", "We agree!");
    } else if (yourResponse == mySecondResponse) {
    	setText("text_area", "We agree again!");
    } else {
    	setText("text_area", "We don't agree :(");
    }`</pre>
</details> 

### Instructions

* Adjust the `if`/`else` statement to make an `if`/`else if`/`else` statement.
* Chain multiple `else if` statements together to create unique responses for at least 5 different colors.
	* Your color bot must have a unique response for the colors blue, red, and green, and for two additional colors of your choice.

<details>
<summary>**Chaining Conditionals**</summary>
We can chain as many `else if`'s together as we want. A chained conditional could look like `if`/`else if`/`else if`/.../`else if`/`else`. The chain always starts with an `if`, ends with and `else`, and has only `else if`'s in between.
</details>

<br/>

markdown_instructions.U3L24 Chatbot Nested Conditionals_markdo:
Here's your digital assistant again! Time to make it a little smarter.

### Instructions

* Add the `contains` function to your digital assistant
* Add a nested conditional to your digital assistant so it can respond to at least two subtopics
* Your nested conditional should include at least 3 `else if` statements.


<details>
<summary>**Example**</summary>
<pre><code>if (contains(input, "subtopic_1")) {
	if (contains(input, "detail_A")) {
    	setText("text_area", "The input contains detail_A and subtopic_1");
    } else if (contains(input, "detail_B")) {
    	setText("text_area", "The input contains detail_B and subtopic_1");
    } else if (contains(input, "detail_C")) {
    	setText("text_area", "The input contains detail_c and subtopic_1");
    }
} else if (contains(input, "subtopic_2")) {
	if (contains(input, "detail_Z")) {
    	setText("text_area", "The input contains detail_Z and subtopic_2"));
    } else if (contains(input, "detail_Y")) {
    	setText("text_area", "The input contains detail_Y and subtopic_2"));
    } else {
    	setText("text_area", "The input contains subtopic_2, but no details"));
    }
} else {
	setText("text_area", "The input doesn't contain any subtopics I know about");
}</code></pre>
</details>

