markdown_instructions.U3L26 Compound Logic_markdown_instructio:
## Multiple Operators

The logical operators AND, OR, and NOT can be combined to make more complicated logic sentences. Generally, if you use more than one type of logical operator, you should put them between parentheses.

<details>
<summary>**Example**</summary>
<pre>`var accurate = true, correct = true, inaccurate = false, incorrect = false;
if (!(inaccurate || incorrect) && (accurate && correct)) {
	setText("text_area", "It must be true!");
} else {
	setText("text_area", "Saddly, it's false.");
}`</pre>
</details>

### Instructions

In the last level, we detected if a command contained the word "bad." That was helpful, but there are lots of other words for bad movies that we need to catch.

* Write a function called isBad that detects the words "bad," "worst," and "terrible."
* If all these phrases are detected, make Movie Bot respond "The top grossing animated and G-rated film in the 2000 decade was Finding Nemo."

